   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LIFE-STUDY OF ZECHARIAH MESSAGE ELEVEN THE PROPHECIES OF ENCOURAGEMENT 3 Scripture Reading: Zech 11</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>In this message we will consider the prophecy in chapter eleven of Zechariah.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>III.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>THE PROPHECY CONCERNING THE LIVING OF ISRAEL</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>UNDER THE OPPRESSION OF THE ROMAN EMPIRE</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The prophecy in Zechariah 11 covers the living of Israel under the oppression of the Roman Empire.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>As we will see, in this chapter there is evidence which proves that it is concerned with the tyranny of the Roman Empire.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>A. The Destruction Carried Out</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>in the Neighborhood of Israel by the Roman Empire</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Verses 1 through 3 reveal the destruction carried out in the neighborhood of Israel by the Roman Empire.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The fire in verse 1 refers to the coming of the Roman Caesar to devastate Lebanon and Jordan.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>B. The Children of Israel</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Falling into Their Neighbors' Hand</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>and into the Hand of Their King</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Israel's living under the tyranny of the Roman Empire is seen in verses 4 through 6.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The children of Israel fell into their neighbors' hand and into the hand of their king.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The neighbors mentioned in verse 6 refer to the subordinate kings and governors of the Roman Empire, such as Herod and Pilate, in the region of Palestine.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The king in verse 6 is Caesar.</S>
